{"link": "http://www.eclipse.org/paho/articles/talkingsmall/", "text": "mqttc = mqtt.Client()\nmqttc.connect(\"m2m.eclipse.org\", 1883, 60)\nmqttc.loop_start()"}
{"link": "http://www.eclipse.org/paho/articles/talkingsmall/", "text": "Here we create our client and tell it to connect to m2m.eclipse.org. That\u2019s the Eclipse public sandbox for M2M developers which has been created to let people experiment with M2M without setting up their own broker. That said, you can easily set up a broker with Mosquitto (http://mosquitto.org/), the open source dedicated MQTT broker, if you wish. Other brokers are available, but it\u2019s worth noting that Mosquitto is also becoming an Eclipse M2M project."}
