{"link": "http://www.eclipse.org/paho/articles/talkingsmall/", "text": "And we can continue doing whatever processing we want after\u2026 in the example, we\u2019ll just idly wait calling Thread.sleep. There\u2019s only one thing missing - we haven\u2019t implemented the methods needed by MqttCallback, and most importantly, the messageArrived callback. This delivers the topic the message has been sent to and the message itself. For now, the code can just print the topic and the message payload:"}
{"link": "http://www.eclipse.org/paho/articles/talkingsmall/", "text": "public void messageArrived(String topic, MqttMessage message) throws Exception\n  {\n    System.out.println (topic + \" \" + new String(message.getPayload()));\n  }"}
{"link": "http://www.eclipse.org/paho/articles/talkingsmall/", "text": "These aren\u2019t the only callbacks needed though, so the code will need to declare the others, even if they only do nothing:"}
{"link": "http://www.eclipse.org/paho/articles/talkingsmall/", "text": "public void connectionLost (Throwable cause) {}\n  public void deliveryComplete(IMqttDeliveryToken token) {}"}
