{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/committees/mqtt/charter.php", "text": "Choices. With a standard protocol, initial choices in devices, networks and suppliers, will not limit choices and adaptability in the future. A standard protocol that supports current and future device payload formats will support deployment, connectivity, and reconfiguration over a wide range of network and server characteristics."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/committees/mqtt/charter.php", "text": "Flexible Integration. Even if highly effective, decoupling techniques between internal device infrastructure and external systems will not see widespread adoption without standardization. With devices and device controllers utilizing a standardized message protocol, a basic publish/subscribe model can support integration with a wide range of established messaging and event processing systems, allowing subscribers to effectively decouple from device and network APIs."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/committees/mqtt/charter.php", "text": "Time to Market. Porting and supporting multiple protocols on multiple platforms tends to inhibit adoption in control and instrumentation systems, which are built using many variations of hardware and software platforms, device types, and networks. Providing an open protocol that scales well from critical embedded systems up to high volume enterprise transaction processing, and one that is data, platform and language independent, will shorten time to market and support new levels of integration."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/committees/mqtt/charter.php", "text": "Skills.  A standard, based on protocol and programming models familiar to both embedded and IT programming communities, will accelerate markets by building on skilled resources that already understand these types of solutions."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/committees/mqtt/charter.php", "text": "Scope of Work of the TC"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/committees/mqtt/charter.php", "text": "The TC will accept the OASIS Standard MQTT Version 3.1.1 as its input specification. The TC will also accept as input a list of issues and recommended changes from the TC Members, incorporating appropriate additional contributions to the TC."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/committees/mqtt/charter.php", "text": "All contributions will be accepted for consideration without any prejudice or restrictions and evaluated based on technical merit in so far as they conform to this charter and its schedule."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The protocol runs over TCP/IP, or over other network\r\nprotocols that provide ordered, lossless, bi-directional connections. Its\r\nfeatures include:"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "\u00b7"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Use of the publish/subscribe message pattern which provides\r\none-to-many message distribution and decoupling of applications."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "\u00b7"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "A messaging transport that is agnostic to the content of the\r\npayload."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "\u00b7"}
