{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Three qualities of service for message delivery:"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "\u00b7"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "\"At most once\", where messages are delivered according\r\nto the best efforts of the operating environment. Message loss can occur. This\r\nlevel could be used, for example, with ambient sensor data where it does not\r\nmatter if an individual reading is lost as the next one will be published soon\r\nafter."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "\u00b7"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "\"At least once\", where messages are assured to arrive\r\nbut duplicates can occur."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "\u00b7"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "\"Exactly once\", where message are assured to arrive\r\nexactly once. This level could be used, for example, with billing systems where\r\nduplicate or lost messages could lead to incorrect charges being applied."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "\u00b7"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "A small transport overhead and protocol exchanges minimized to\r\nreduce network traffic."}
