{"link": "http://www.eclipse.org/paho/articles/talkingsmall/", "text": "Which would mean that messages for both \u201cbbbexample/tmp36/mv\u201d and \u201cbbbexample/tmp36/c\u201d would arrive at the messageArrived method. It would be up to the code to distinguish between the topics and decide what action it wants to take. Other examples of topic subscriptions would be \u201cbbbexample/#\u201d, which would match any message sent to a subtopic of \u201cbbbexample\u201d and \u201cbbbexample/+/c\u201d which would match messages to any immediate child of \u201cbbbexample\u201d which had an immediate child \u201cc\u201d."}
