{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Eclipse download increases by more than 100% in the last year"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "September 11, 2019 12:00 AM"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Downloads have increased by more than 3.3 millions compared to last years release. The Eclipse Photon release was downloaded 2.8 million times. The Eclipse 2019-06 release was downloaded 6.1 millions times.\nGreat news for the Eclipse IDE!\nThat is more than 100% increase from June 2018 to the June 2019 release. While it is hard to speculate why this is happening we think that the increased stability and performance as well as modern solutions based on the language server for JavaScript and Rust have changed the perception of Eclipse."}
