{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Welcome to the Future of Cloud Native Java"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "by Mike Milinkovich at September 10, 2019 11:00 AM"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Today, with the release of"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Jakarta EE 8"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": ", we\u2019ve entered a new era in Java innovation."}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Under an open, vendor-neutral process, a diverse community of the world\u2019s leading Java organizations, hundreds of dedicated developers, and Eclipse Foundation staff have delivered the Jakarta EE 8 Full Platform, Web Profiles, and related TCKs, as well as Eclipse GlassFish 5.1 certified as a Jakarta EE 8 compatible implementation."}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "To say this a big deal is an understatement. With 18 different"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "member organizations"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": ", over 160 new committers, 43"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "projects"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": ", and a codebase of over 61 million lines of code in 129 Git repositories, this was truly a massive undertaking \u2014 even by the Eclipse community\u2019s standards. There are far too many people to thank individually here, so I\u2019ll say many thanks to everyone in the Jakarta EE community who played a role in achieving this industry milestone."}
{"link": "https://www.eclipse.org/proposals/technology.paho/", "text": "The Paho project will have relationships with Equinox and\nother Eclipse projects, including the Koneki project and other tooling projects\nused by embedded, enterprise and Web developers."}
{"link": "https://www.eclipse.org/proposals/technology.paho/", "text": "Initial Contribution"}
{"link": "https://www.eclipse.org/proposals/technology.paho/", "text": "The initial code contribution to Paho will include \u00a0Java and C client-side implementations\nthe"}
{"link": "https://www.eclipse.org/proposals/technology.paho/", "text": "MQTT\nprotocol"}
{"link": "https://www.eclipse.org/proposals/technology.paho/", "text": ", contributed by IBM. MQTT is a lightweight publish/subscribe\nprotocol designed for mobile and remote devices, wireless connectivity, and dealing\nwith lossy, constrained and/or intermittent network characteristics."}
{"link": "https://www.eclipse.org/proposals/technology.paho/", "text": "Eurotech will contribute\nthe implementation of a framework and sample applications which device and\nclient developers can use when integrating and testing Paho messaging\ncomponents. This will require the setup of an appropriate M2M test server which\nwill be worked out with the Eclipse Foundation. The architecture for this\nsandbox will be coordinated with the M2M Industry Working Group."}
