{"link": "https://www.eclipse.org/paho/components/testing/", "text": "MQTT Conformance/Interoperability Testing"}
{"link": "https://www.eclipse.org/paho/components/testing/", "text": "The aim of this project is to create a means by which it is easy to test both MQTT servers and client libraries, to\nensure"}
{"link": "https://www.eclipse.org/paho/components/testing/", "text": "they conform to the"}
{"link": "https://www.eclipse.org/paho/components/testing/", "text": "MQTT 3.1.1 standard"}
{"link": "https://www.eclipse.org/paho/components/testing/", "text": "and hence they can interoperate with each other, with the minimum of misunderstandings."}
{"link": "https://www.eclipse.org/paho/components/testing/", "text": "The test material is all written in Python version 3 (Python 2.x is not sufficient).  The component of the test material are:"}
{"link": "https://www.eclipse.org/paho/components/testing/", "text": "an MQTT conformance statements spreadsheet, extracted from the standard"}
{"link": "https://www.eclipse.org/paho/components/testing/", "text": "a test broker, against which client tests can be run"}
{"link": "https://www.eclipse.org/paho/components/testing/", "text": "a test client, for very basic testing of MQTT server 3.1.1 support"}
{"link": "https://www.eclipse.org/paho/components/testing/", "text": "a model-based testing package, which will be used to generate the full tests, in due course"}
