{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": ") and can easily integrate them into their solution. But on the cloud side of things, building blocks become much more complex to integrate, and harder to understand."}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Of course, the \u201cgetting started\u201d experience is extremely important. You can simply"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "download an Eclipse IDE package"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": ", tailored towards your context (Java, Modelling, Rust, \u2026), and are up and running within minutes. We don\u2019t want you to design your deployment descriptors first, and then let you figure out how to start up your distributed cluster. Otherwise \u201cgetting started\u201d will become a week long task. And a rather frustrating one."}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Getting started. Quickly!"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "During the"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Eclipse IoT face-to-face meeting in Berlin"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": ", early this year, the Eclipse IoT working group discussed various ideas. How can we enable interested parties to get started, with as little effort as possible. And still, give you full control. Not only with a single component, which doesn\u2019t provide much benefit on its own. But get you started with a complete solution, which solves actual IoT related problems."}
