{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Challenges, moving towards an IoT solution"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "A much tougher question was: how do we structure this, from a project perspective. During the meeting, it soon turned out, there would be two good initial candidates for \u201cstacks\u201d or \u201cgroups of projects\u201d, which we would like to create."}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "It also turned out that we would need some \u201cglue\u201d components for a package like that. Even though it may only be a script here, or a \u201creadme\u201d file there. Some artifacts just don\u2019t fit into either of those projects. And what about \u201cin development\u201d versions of the projects? How can you point people towards a stable deployment, only using a stable (released) group of projects, when scripts and readme\u2019s are spread all over the place, in different branches."}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "A combination of \u201c"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Hono"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": ","}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Ditto"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "&"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Hawkbit"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "\u201d seemed like an ideal IoT solution to start with. People from various companies already work across those three projects, using them in combination for their own purpose. So, why not build on that?"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "But in addition to all those technical challenges, the governance of this effort is an aspect to consider. We did not want to exclude other Eclipse IoT projects, simply by starting out with \u201cHono, Ditto, and Hawkbit\u201d. We only wanted to create \u201can\u201d Eclipse IoT solution, and not \u201cthe\u201d Eclipse IoT solution. The whole Eclipse IoT ecosystem is much too diverse, to force our initial idea on everyone else. So what if someone comes up with an additional group of Eclipse IoT projects? Or what if someone would like to add a new project to an existing deployment?"}
