{"link": "https://www.eclipse.org/paho/clients/java/", "text": "The Paho Java Client is an MQTT client library written in Java\n            for developing applications that run on the JVM or other Java\n            compatible platforms such as Android"}
{"link": "https://www.eclipse.org/paho/clients/java/", "text": "The Paho Java Client provides two APIs: MqttAsyncClient provides\n            a fully asychronous API where completion of activities is notified\n            via registered callbacks. MqttClient is a synchronous wrapper\n            around MqttAsyncClient where functions appear synchronous to the\n            application."}
