{"link": "https://www.infoq.com/articles/practical-mqtt-with-paho/", "text": ". We then tell the client to connect. Now we can create an"}
{"link": "https://www.infoq.com/articles/practical-mqtt-with-paho/", "text": "MqttMessage"}
{"link": "https://www.infoq.com/articles/practical-mqtt-with-paho/", "text": "and we set its payload to a simple string. Notice that we convert the string to bytes as setPayload only takes an array of bytes. We're relying on the default settings for"}
{"link": "https://www.infoq.com/articles/practical-mqtt-with-paho/", "text": "MqttMessage"}
{"link": "https://www.infoq.com/articles/practical-mqtt-with-paho/", "text": "to set the various other parameters. Next, we publish the message and it's here we need to introduce topics."}
{"link": "https://www.infoq.com/articles/practical-mqtt-with-paho/", "text": "To avoid the obvious problem of every client getting every message published by every other client, MQTT messages are published with what are called"}
{"link": "https://www.infoq.com/articles/practical-mqtt-with-paho/", "text": "topics"}
{"link": "https://www.infoq.com/articles/practical-mqtt-with-paho/", "text": ". A topic is a structured string that defines a location in a namespace with"}
{"link": "https://www.infoq.com/articles/practical-mqtt-with-paho/", "text": "\"/\""}
{"link": "https://www.infoq.com/articles/practical-mqtt-with-paho/", "text": "used to delimit levels of that namespace's hierarchy. A topic could be, for example,"}
{"link": "https://www.infoq.com/articles/practical-mqtt-with-paho/", "text": "\"/pumpmonitor/pumps/1/level\""}
