{"link": "https://www.infoq.com/articles/practical-mqtt-with-paho/", "text": "Connection options"}
{"link": "https://www.infoq.com/articles/practical-mqtt-with-paho/", "text": "When connecting to the broker, there are a number of options that can be set which are encapsulated in the"}
{"link": "https://www.infoq.com/articles/practical-mqtt-with-paho/", "text": "MqttConnectOptions"}
{"link": "https://www.infoq.com/articles/practical-mqtt-with-paho/", "text": "class. These include the keep-alive interval for maintaining the connection with the broker, the retry interval for delivering messages, the connection timeout period, the clean session flag, the connection's will and, for the Java side of the code, which"}
{"link": "https://www.infoq.com/articles/practical-mqtt-with-paho/", "text": "SocketFactory"}
{"link": "https://www.infoq.com/articles/practical-mqtt-with-paho/", "text": "to use."}
{"link": "https://www.infoq.com/articles/practical-mqtt-with-paho/", "text": "If we modify our client so it reads:"}
{"link": "https://www.infoq.com/articles/practical-mqtt-with-paho/", "text": "import org.eclipse.paho.client.mqttv3.MqttConnectOptions;\r\n  ...\r\n  MqttConnectOptions options;\r\n  ...\r\n    client = new MqttClient(\"tcp://localhost:1883\", \"pahomqttpublish2\");\r\n    options = new MqttConnectOptions();\r\n    client.connect(options);"}
{"link": "https://www.infoq.com/articles/practical-mqtt-with-paho/", "text": "We can experiment with the connection options. For this example, the interesting options are the clean flag and the will. When messages are sent with a QoS above 0, steps need to be taken to ensure that when a client reconnects it doesn't repeat messages and resumes the previous session with the broker. But if you want to ensure that all that state information is discarded at connection and disconnection, you set the clean session flag to true. How does the broker identify clients you may ask? Through that client id is the answer and is also the reason why you need to ensure that client ids are different."}
