{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "The Xtext team has released version 2.19.0 of Eclipse Xtext & Xtend. The current version is mainly a maintenance release. After working hard on some new features in the past releases, it was time for summer vacation during the current release period and for some focus on build engineering tasks. Still over 350 pull requests made it into the short release period."}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Eclipse\u2019s new build infrastructure JIRO"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "The Eclipse Foundation\u2019s build engineers worked on a new build infrastructure called"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "JIRO (Jenkins Instances Running on OpenShift)"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": ". The Xtext project joined early the efforts on preparing a migration to the new infrastructure. However, now it was time and the Eclipse Foundation asked to finally shut down the old build server and to switch over to the new infrastructure. While we were already done with the main build jobs, there were still quite some supportive build jobs for release engineering that had to be migrated."}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Luckily, the itemis Xtext team could acquire Nico Prediger from the itemis DevOps staff to support the efforts on build engineering tasks. With his support, we could finalize the work and finally replace the old Jenkins instance."}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "As a result, Xtext builds fine now on its new JIRO instance at"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "https://ci.eclipse.org/xtext/"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "and was released the first time on the new infra."}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Keeping the software stack up-to-date"}
