{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Xtext builds upon a quite huge software stack, and several components are released within each release period. We try to keep them all on the latest state as far as we can. Of course, for each used component we have to test the compatibility of each upgrade."}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "The most notable upgrades this time are Guava and Gradle:"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "The Guava version 21.0 that we used before had a security problem that was issued as"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "CVE-2018-10237"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": ". This forced Xtext as well as other dependent Eclipse projects to upgrade to a recent version of Guava. For the Eclipse 2019-09 simultaneous release, the delivered Guava version is now 27.1.0. All builds descriptors, wizards, and projects have been updated to use Guava 27.1.0 now."}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "The Guava upgrade also affected the MWE project, which employed the upgrade with its recent release. As a consequence, Xtext upgraded to MWE 2.11."}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Xtext has been updated to use"}
