{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Each time a Client sends a new packet of one of these\r\ntypes it MUST assign it a currently unused Packet Identifier"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-2.3.1-2]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If a Client\r\nre-sends a particular Control Packet, then it MUST use the same Packet Identifier\r\nin subsequent re-sends of that packet. The Packet Identifier becomes available\r\nfor reuse after the Client has processed the corresponding acknowledgement\r\npacket. In the case of a QoS 1 PUBLISH this is the corresponding PUBACK; in the\r\ncase of QoS 2 it is PUBCOMP. For SUBSCRIBE or UNSUBSCRIBE it is the\r\ncorresponding SUBACK or UNSUBACK"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-2.3.1-3]"}
