{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Eclipse light theme for TM4E"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "TM4E can be used to apply different syntax highlighting to the editor.\nWe provide a configuration file that specifies how certain words inside the editor should look.\nIt also gives the option to select what theme to use.\nThere are different light and dark themes available, like"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Solarized Light"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "or the classic Eclipse Java editor theme."}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "I provided a patch to add some missing styles to the latter to make it look more like the classic theme.\nThis is what it looks like now:"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "See"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "eclipse/tm4e#215"}
