{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "KubeCon Shanghai 2019: Cloud Native at China Scale"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "by Chris Aniszczyk at July 29, 2019 04:08 PM"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Last month, we held KubeCon + Cloud NativeCon in Shanghai, one of the largest open source events in China. Recently, we published the"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "conference transparency report"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "detailing how the 3500 person event went but I\u2019d like to share a couple take aways as someone who has been traveling to China quite a bit the last few years."}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Another record-breaking event!"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "#KubeCon"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "+"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "#CloudNativeCon"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "+"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "0"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Server MUST validate\r\nthat the reserved flag in the CONNECT Control Packet is set to zero and\r\ndisconnect the Client if it is not zero"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.2-3]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "3.1.2.4 Clean Session"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Position:"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "bit 1 of the\r\nConnect Flags byte."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "This bit specifies the handling of the Session state."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Client and Server can store Session state to enable reliable messaging to\r\ncontinue across a sequence of Network Connections. This bit is used to control\r\nthe lifetime of the Session state."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If CleanSession is set\r\nto 0, the Server MUST resume communications with the Client based on state from\r\nthe current Session (as identified by the Client identifier). If there is no\r\nSession associated with the Client identifier the Server MUST create a new\r\nSession. The Client and Server MUST store the Session after the Client and\r\nServer are disconnected"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.2-4]"}
