{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "July 26, 2019"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Cloud Native at China Scale"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "The scale of operating a popular service in China can be wild when you serve a billion users. This forces many of these companies to operate in a cloud native fashion, similar to their internet scale peers in Silicon Valley. I strongly believe we will see more interesting open source technology born in China over the next decade as they deal with scaling issues, similar to how a lot of internet scale open source technology was born from Google and other SV companies that had to support a larger user base. I highly recommend this great"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "interview from Kevin Xu"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "After the disconnection of a Session that had\r\nCleanSession set to 0, the Server MUST store further QoS 1 and QoS 2 messages\r\nthat match any subscriptions that the client had at the time of disconnection\r\nas part of the Session state"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "["}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "MQTT-3"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": ".1.2-5]."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "It MAY also store QoS 0 messages that meet\r\nthe same criteria."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If\r\nCleanSession is set to 1, the Client and Server MUST discard any previous\r\nSession and start a new one. This Session lasts as long as the Network\r\nConnection. State data associated with this Session MUST NOT be reused in any subsequent\r\nSession"}
