{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Eclipse has mechanism to recognize if the workspace to be used is created with older Eclipse version."}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "In such case, to be safe, Eclipse shows dialog like:"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "As of today (Eclipse 4.12 M1), if you click on \"Cancel\" button, Eclipse will behave differently, depending on the use cases \"history\":"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "A. If the workbench was not started yet:"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "3.1.2.5 Will Flag"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Position:"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "bit 2 of the Connect Flags."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the Will Flag is set to 1 this indicates that, if the Connect request is\r\naccepted, a Will Message MUST be stored on the Server and associated with the\r\nNetwork Connection. The Will Message MUST be published when the Network Connection\r\nis subsequently closed unless the Will Message has been deleted by the Server\r\non receipt of a DISCONNECT Packet"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.2-8]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Situations in which the Will Message is published include,\r\nbut are not limited to:"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "An I/O error or network failure detected by the Server."}
