{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "If Eclipse was started"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "with"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "\"-data\" argument pointing to the incompatible workspace, Eclipse will show \"Older Workspace Version\" dialog above and\u00a0by clicking on \"Cancel\" it will"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "terminate"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "(instead of offering to select another workspace)."}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "B. If the workbench was\u00a0started:"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "If user selects"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "compatible"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "workspace in the \"File -> Switch Workspace\" dialog, Eclipse restarts fine."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Client fails to communicate within the Keep Alive\r\n     time."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Client closes the Network Connection without first\r\n     sending a DISCONNECT Packet."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Server closes the Network Connection because of a\r\n     protocol error."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the Will Flag is set to\r\n1, the Will QoS and Will Retain fields in the Connect Flags will be used by the\r\nServer, and the Will Topic and Will Message fields MUST be present in the\r\npayload"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.2-9]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Will Message MUST be\r\nremoved from the stored Session state in the Server once it has been published\r\nor the Server has received a DISCONNECT packet from the Client"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.2-10]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the Will Flag is set to 0\r\nthe Will QoS and Will Retain fields in the Connect Flags MUST be set to zero\r\nand the Will Topic and Will Message fields MUST NOT be present in the payload"}
