{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "This behavior is inconvenient (at least), so we have"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "bug 538830"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "."}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Fix Proposal #1"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "The proposal is, that"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "independently"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "on the way Eclipse was started, if user clicks on the \"Cancel\" button in the \"Older Workspace Version\" dialog, we"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "always"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.2-11]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the Will Flag is set to\r\n0, a Will Message MUST NOT be published when this Network Connection ends"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.2-12]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Server SHOULD publish Will\r\nMessages promptly. In the case of a Server shutdown or failure the server MAY\r\ndefer publication of Will Messages until a subsequent restart. If this happens\r\nthere might be a delay between the time the server experienced failure and a\r\nWill Message being published."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "3.1.2.6 Will QoS"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Position:"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "bits 4 and 3 of the Connect Flags."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "These two bits specify the QoS level to be used when publishing the Will\r\nMessage."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the Will Flag is set to\r\n0, then the Will QoS MUST be set to 0"}
