{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Chess game implemented in N4JS with React"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "The chess game app implements the following requirements:"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "When the chess application is started, a chess board of 8x8 squares shall be showed containing 16 white pieces and 16 black pieces in their initial positions."}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "A player in turn shall be able to use the mouse to pick one of the pieces that she/he wants to move. A picked piece shall be clearly recognisable. Moreover, to aid players, especially beginners, whenever a piece is picked, all possible valid destination squares shall be visually highlighted as well."}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "In addition to the game board, there shall be a game information area that shows which player is in turn. Moreover, the game information area shall show a complete history of the game protocolling each move made by the players. As a bonus, jumping back to a previous state of the history shall be possible."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If\r\nthe Keep Alive value is non-zero and the Server does not receive a Control\r\nPacket from the Client within one and a half times the Keep Alive time period,\r\nit MUST disconnect the Network Connection to the Client as if the network had\r\nfailed"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.2-24]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If a Client does not receive a\r\nPINGRESP Packet within a reasonable amount of time after it has sent a PINGREQ,\r\nit SHOULD close the Network Connection to the Server."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "A Keep Alive value of zero (0)\r\nhas the effect of turning off the keep alive mechanism. This means that, in\r\nthis case, the Server is not required to disconnect the Client on the grounds\r\nof inactivity."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Note that a Server is permitted to disconnect a Client that it determines to be\r\ninactive or non-responsive at any time, regardless of the Keep Alive value\r\nprovided by that Client."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Non normative\r\ncomment"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The actual value\r\nof the Keep Alive is application specific; typically this is a few minutes. The\r\nmaximum value is 18 hours 12 minutes and 15 seconds."}
