{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Industrial-Scale Collaboration for the Business Win"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "by Mike Milinkovich at July 15, 2019 02:40 PM"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Marc Andreessen once famously said, \u201c"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Software is eating the world"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": ".\u201d He was right, software gobbled up industry sectors as varied as financial services, automotive, mining, healthcare, and entertainment. Companies of all sizes have leveraged software to improve their business processes and adapt products to a digital economy. And then a funny thing happened: open source ate software."}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "From startups to the world\u2019s large corporations, commercial software is built on and with open source. In fact, open source now comprises 80 to 90 percent of the code in a typical software application. Today,"}
