{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Clients typically wait for a CONNACK Packet, However, if the Client exploits\r\nits freedom to send Control Packets before it receives a CONNACK,\u00a0it might\r\nsimplify the Client implementation as it does not have to police the connected\r\nstate. The Client accepts that any data that it sends before it receives a\r\nCONNACK packet from the Server\u00a0will not be processed if the Server rejects\r\nthe connection."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "3.2 CONNACK \u2013 Acknowledge connection request"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The CONNACK Packet is the packet sent by the Server in\r\nresponse to a CONNECT Packet received from a Client."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The first packet sent from the Server to the Client MUST be a CONNACK\r\nPacket"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.2.0-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the Client does not receive a\r\nCONNACK Packet from the Server within a reasonable amount of time, the Client\r\nSHOULD close the Network Connection. A \"reasonable\" amount of time\r\ndepends on the type of application and the communications infrastructure."}
