{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The recipient of a Control Packet\r\nthat contains the DUP flag set to 1 cannot assume that it has seen an earlier\r\ncopy of this packet."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Non normative comment"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "It is important to note that the DUP\r\nflag refers to the Control Packet itself and not to the Application Message\r\nthat it contains. When using QoS 1, it is possible for a Client to receive a\r\nPUBLISH Packet with DUP flag set to 0 that contains a repetition of an\r\nApplication Message that it received earlier, but with a different Packet\r\nIdentifier. Section 2.3.1 provides more information about Packet Identifiers."}
