{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "A prototype implementation shows all error, warning, and info annotations (\u201cbubbles\u201d in the left ruler) in Eclipse Java editor as inline text. Thus, we don\u2019t have to use the mouse to view the error message. The error messages update live with changes in the editor."}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Screencast showing the live effect"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "I\u2019m an avid keyboard user. If I have to touch the mouse, something is wrong. Eclise has tons of shortcuts to ease your live, and I use and enjoy them every day."}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "However, if I had an error message in e.g. my Java file, and I couldn\u2019t anticipate the error, I had several bad choices:"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Opening the"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Problems"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "view and navigating to the current error (entries in the  Problems view are called \u201cmarkers\u201d by Eclipse)"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Moving the mouse over the annotation in the left ruler (\u201cannotation\u201d in Eclipse lingo)"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Guessing"}
