{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Not so long ago, Angelo Zerr and others implemented"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "code mining"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "in Eclipse. This feature displays additional information within a text file without changing the actual contents of the file. Sounds like a natural fit for my problem!"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "I first tried to implement the error code mining based on markers, ("}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Bug 540443"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "). This works in general. However, markers are bound to the"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "persisted state"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "of a file, i.e. how a file is saved to disk. So they are only updated on saving."}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Most editors in Eclipse are more interactive than that: They update their error information based on the"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "dirty state"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "When a new subscription is established, the last\r\nretained message, if any, on each matching topic name MUST be sent to the\r\nsubscriber"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.3.1-6]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the Server\r\nreceives a QoS 0 message with the RETAIN flag set to 1 it MUST discard any\r\nmessage previously retained for that topic. It SHOULD store the new QoS 0\r\nmessage as the new retained message for that topic, but MAY choose to discard\r\nit at any time - if this happens there will be no retained message for that\r\ntopic"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.3.1-7]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": ". See Section 4.1 for more information on storing state."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "When sending a PUBLISH\r\nPacket to a Client the Server MUST set the RETAIN flag to 1 if a message is\r\nsent as a result of a new subscription being made by a Client"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.3.1-8]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "."}
