{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "https://opensource.com/article/19/4/ways-support-sustain-open-source"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "To make sure open source continues to thrive, we all need to find ways to sustain the communities and projects we depend on"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "The success of open source continues to grow; surveys show that the"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "majority of companies"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "use some form of open source,"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "99% of enterprises see open source as important"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": ", and"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "almost half of developers"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "are contributing\u00a0back. It\u2019s important to note that companies aren\u2019t contributing to open source for purely altruistic reasons. Recent"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "research"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "from Harvard\u00a0shows that open source-contributing companies capture up to 100% more productive value from open source than companies that do not contribute back. Another research"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "study"}
