{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Eclipse Foundation Specification Process"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "(EFSP) a single open source specification project has a dedicated project team of committers to create and maintain one or more specifications. The cycle of creation and maintenance extends across multiple versions of the specification, and so while individual members may come and go, the team remains and it is that team that is responsible for the every version of that specification that is created."}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "The first step in managing how intellectual property rights flow through a specification is to define the range of the work encompassed by the specification. Per the Eclipse"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Intellectual Property Policy"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": ", this range of work (referred to as the"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "scope"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": ") needs to be well-defined and captured. Once defined, the scope is effectively locked down (changes to the scope are possible but rare, and must be carefully managed; the scope of a specification can be tweaked and changed, but doing so requires approval from the"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Jakarta EE Working Group\u2019s"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Specification Committee"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": ")."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "3.6.3 Payload"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The PUBREL Packet has no payload."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "3.6.4 Actions"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "This is fully described in Section 4.3.3."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "3.7 PUBCOMP \u2013 Publish complete\r\n(QoS 2 publish received, part 3)"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The PUBCOMP Packet is the response to a PUBREL Packet. It is\r\nthe fourth and final packet of the QoS 2 protocol exchange."}
