{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "April 05, 2019 05:07 AM"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "The official Scout version 9 has been released as part of the Eclipse simultaneous release 2019-03 and is now publicly available. In this article we highlight some of the new features such as improved responsiveness, support for OpenJDK and more."}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "With the Eclipse simultaneous release 2019-03, the new Scout version 9.0 has been released. As usual, it contains a lot of changes. We are happy to share some of the highlights with you. The complete release notes can be found"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "here"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "."}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Support for OpenJDK and newer Java Versions"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Long requested and finally here: Scout now supports running on OpenJDK, and on Java versions up to 11. Note that this requires a bit of work on the side of developers; and RedHat's OpenJDK version is not compatible out of the box due to missing elliptic curves. For more details, see the Java 11 section in the"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "release notes"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "and the"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "migration guide"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "3.7.3 Payload"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The PUBCOMP Packet has no payload."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "3.7.4 Actions"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "This is fully described in Section 4.3.3."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "3.8 SUBSCRIBE - Subscribe to\r\ntopics"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The SUBSCRIBE Packet is sent from the Client to the Server to\r\ncreate one or more Subscriptions. Each Subscription registers a Client\u2019s\r\ninterest in one or more Topics. The Server sends PUBLISH Packets to the Client\r\nin order to forward Application Messages that were published to Topics that\r\nmatch these Subscriptions. The SUBSCRIBE Packet also specifies (for each\r\nSubscription) the maximum QoS with which the Server can send Application\r\nMessages to the Client."}
