{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Widget 2: Popup"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "With the new \"Popup\" (also known as popover on some platforms), you can display additional information in an overlay. You have many options to embed widgets here - we can't wait to see what you do with it!"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "The Popup has the following features:"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Take any widget you like and open it in a Popup by using the WidgetPopup."}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Use any widget you like as anchor and align the Popup around it."}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Decide whether you want to point the Popup to the anchor by using the property withArrow."}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Control the behavior of what should happen if there is not enough space to display the whole Popup using various properties."}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Choose how the popup should react when the user clicks on the outside or on the anchor."}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "try out all the widgets in our widget app"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Changed property lookup order"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "In many technologies such as Docker or Kubernetes, changing the configuration without having to create a new deployment is essential. To support this in Scout, the lookup order for Scout properties has been adjusted: It now allows overriding properties in the configuration file by using environment variables."}
