{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The payload of a SUBSCRIBE Packet contains a list of Topic Filters\r\nindicating the Topics to which the Client wants to subscribe."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Topic Filters in a SUBSCRIBE packet payload MUST\r\nbe UTF-8 encoded strings as defined in Section"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "1.5.3"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.8.3-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": ".\r\nA Server SHOULD support Topic filters that contain the wildcard characters\r\ndefined in Section"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "4.7.1"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If it chooses not to support topic filters that\r\ncontain wildcard characters it MUST reject any Subscription request whose\r\nfilter contains them"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.8.3-2]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": ". Each\r\nfilter is followed by a byte called the Requested QoS. This gives the maximum\r\nQoS level at which the Server can send Application Messages to the Client."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The payload of a SUBSCRIBE\r\npacket MUST contain at least one Topic Filter / QoS pair. A SUBSCRIBE packet\r\nwith no payload is a protocol violation"}
