{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "3.10.4 Response"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Topic Filters (whether they\r\ncontain wildcards or not) supplied in an UNSUBSCRIBE packet MUST be compared character-by-character\r\nwith the current set of Topic Filters held by the Server for the Client. If any\r\nfilter matches exactly then its owning Subscription is deleted, otherwise no\r\nadditional processing occurs"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.10.4-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If a Server deletes a Subscription:"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "It MUST stop adding any\r\n     new messages for delivery to the Client"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.10.4-2]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "It MUST complete the\r\n     delivery of any QoS 1 or QoS 2 messages which it has started to send to\r\n     the Client"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.10.4-3]"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/amqp/soleconn/v1.0/soleconn-v1.0.html"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Scott Schram"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Sebastian Benz"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Sebastian Zarnekow"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Serge Beauchamp"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Seva Lapsha"}
{"link": "https://planeteclipse.org/planet/", "text": "Sharon Corbett"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "It MAY continue to deliver any existing messages buffered\r\n     for delivery to the Client."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Server MUST respond to an UNSUBSUBCRIBE\r\nrequest by sending an UNSUBACK packet. The UNSUBACK Packet MUST have the same\r\nPacket Identifier as the UNSUBSCRIBE Packet"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.10.4-4]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Even where no Topic Subscriptions are deleted,\r\nthe Server MUST respond with an UNSUBACK"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.10.4-5]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If a Server receives an\r\nUNSUBSCRIBE packet that contains multiple Topic Filters it MUST handle that\r\npacket as if it had received a sequence of multiple UNSUBSCRIBE packets, except\r\nthat it sends just one UNSUBACK response"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "."}
