{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "It is necessary for the Client and Server to store Session\r\nstate in order to provide Quality of Service guarantees."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Client and Server MUST store Session state for\r\nthe entire duration of the Session"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.1.0-1]"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "DOCX"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "XML schemas"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Distribution ZIP file"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "OASIS Biometric Services (BIOSERV) TC"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Cite as:"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "[BIAS-Profile-v2.0]"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Biometric Identity Assurance Services (BIAS) Soap Profile Version 2.0"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Edited by Kevin Mangold and Karen Marshall. 11 July 2017. OASIS Committee Specification 01."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/bioserv/BIAS/v2.0/cs01/BIAS-v2.0-cs01.html"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "A Session MUST last at least as long it has an\r\nactive Network Connection"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.1.0-2]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Retained messages do not form part of the Session state in\r\nthe Server. The Server SHOULD retain such messages until deleted by a Client."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Non normative comment"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The storage capabilities of Client\r\nand Server implementations will of course have limits in terms of capacity and\r\nmay be subject to administrative policies such as the maximum time that Session\r\nstate is stored between Network Connections. Stored Session state can be\r\ndiscarded as a result of an administrator action, including an automated response\r\nto defined conditions. This has the effect of terminating the Session. These\r\nactions might be prompted by resource constraints or for other operational\r\nreasons. It is prudent to evaluate the storage capabilities of the Client and\r\nServer to ensure that they are sufficient."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Non normative comment"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "It is possible that hardware or\r\nsoftware failures may result in loss or corruption of Session state stored by\r\nthe Client or Server."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Non normative comment"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Normal operation of the Client of\r\nServer could mean that stored state is lost or corrupted because of\r\nadministrator action,\u00a0hardware failure or software failure. An\r\nadministrator action could be an automated response to defined conditions. These\r\nactions might be prompted by resource constraints or for other operational\r\nreasons.\u00a0For example the server might determine that based on external\r\nknowledge, a message or messages can no longer be delivered to any current or\r\nfuture client."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Non normative comment"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Latest version:"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/bioserv/BIAS/v2.0/BIAS-v2.0.html"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "July 2017"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Voting History"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Business Document Envelope Version 1.0"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "An MQTT user should evaluate the\r\nstorage capabilities of the MQTT Client and Server implementations to ensure\r\nthat they are sufficient for their needs."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "4.1.1 Non normative example"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "For example, a user wishing to gather electricity meter\r\nreadings may decide that they need to use QoS 1 messages because they need to\r\nprotect the readings against loss over the network, however they may have\r\ndetermined that the power supply is sufficiently reliable that the data in the\r\nClient and Server can be stored in volatile memory without too much risk of its\r\nloss."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Conversely a parking meter payment application provider\r\nmight decide that there are no circumstances where a payment message can be\r\nlost so they require that all data are force written to non-volatile memory\r\nbefore it is transmitted across the network."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "4.2 Network"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Connections"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The MQTT protocol requires an underlying transport that\r\nprovides an ordered, lossless, stream of bytes from the Client to Server and\r\nServer to Client."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Non normative comment"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The transport protocol used to\r\ncarry MQTT 3.1 was TCP/IP as defined in"}
