{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "TCP ports 8883 and 1883 are\r\nregistered with IANA for MQTT TLS and non TLS communication respectively."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Connectionless network transports such as"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "User Datagram\r\nProtocol"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "(UDP) are not suitable on their own because they might\r\nlose or reorder data."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "4.3\r\nQuality of Service levels and protocol flows"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "MQTT delivers Application Messages according to the Quality\r\nof Service (QoS) levels defined here. The delivery protocol is symmetric, in\r\nthe description below the Client and Server can each take the role of either\r\nSender or Receiver. The delivery protocol is concerned solely with the delivery\r\nof an application message from a single Sender to a single Receiver. When the\r\nServer is delivering an Application Message to more than one Client, each\r\nClient is treated independently. The QoS level used to deliver an Application\r\nMessage outbound to the Client could differ from that of the inbound\r\nApplication Message."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The non-normative flow diagrams in the following sections\r\nare intended to show possible implementation approaches."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "4.3.1 QoS 0: At most once\r\ndelivery"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "August 2015"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Voting History"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Business Document Envelope Version 1.1"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Committee Specification 01"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "HTML"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "PDF"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "XML"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "BDE Model"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The message is delivered according to the capabilities of\r\nthe underlying network. No response is sent by the receiver and no retry is\r\nperformed by the sender. The message arrives at the receiver either once or not\r\nat all."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "In the QoS 0 delivery\r\nprotocol, the Sender"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "\u00b7"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "MUST send a PUBLISH packet with\r\nQoS=0, DUP=0"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.3.1-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "In the QoS 0 delivery protocol, the Receiver"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "\u00b7"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Accepts ownership of the message when it receives the PUBLISH\r\npacket."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Figure 4.1 \u2013 QoS 0\r\nprotocol flow diagram, non normative example"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Sender Action"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Control Packet"}
