{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Edited by G. Ken Holman and Kenneth Bengtsson. 05 December 2016. OASIS Committee Specification 01."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Receiver Action"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "PUBLISH QoS 0,\r\n  DUP=0"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "---------->"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Deliver Application\r\n  Message to appropriate onward recipient(s)"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "4.3.2"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "QoS 1: At least once\r\ndelivery"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "This quality of service ensures\r\nthat the message arrives at the receiver at least once. A QoS 1 PUBLISH Packet\r\nhas a Packet Identifier in its variable header and is acknowledged by a PUBACK\r\nPacket. Section 2.3.1 provides more information about Packet Identifiers."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "In the QoS 1 delivery\r\nprotocol, the Sender"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "\u00b7"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "MUST assign an unused Packet Identifier\r\neach time it has a new Application Message to publish."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "\u00b7"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "MUST send a PUBLISH Packet\r\ncontaining this Packet Identifier with QoS=1, DUP=0."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "\u00b7"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "MUST treat the PUBLISH Packet as \u201cunacknowledged\u201d\r\nuntil it has received the corresponding PUBACK packet from the receiver. See\r\nSection"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/bdxr/bdx-bde/v1.1/cs01/bdx-bde-v1.1-cs01.html"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": ". Latest version:"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/bdxr/bdx-bde/v1.1/bdx-bde-v1.1.html"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "December 2016"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Voting History"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "4.4"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "for a discussion of unacknowledged messages."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.3.2-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Packet Identifier becomes\r\navailable for reuse once the Sender has received the PUBACK Packet."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Note that a Sender is permitted\r\nto send further PUBLISH Packets with different Packet Identifiers while it is\r\nwaiting to receive acknowledgements."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "In the QoS 1 delivery\r\nprotocol, the Receiver"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "MUST respond with a PUBACK\r\n     Packet containing the Packet Identifier from the incoming PUBLISH Packet,\r\n     having accepted ownership of the Application Message"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "After it has sent a PUBACK\r\n     Packet the Receiver MUST treat any incoming PUBLISH packet that contains\r\n     the same Packet Identifier as being a new publication, irrespective of the\r\n     setting of its DUP flag."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.3.2-2]"}
