{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": ". Edited by Jacques Durand, Adrian Otto, Gilbert Pilz, and Tom Rutt."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "15 May 2018. OASIS Committee Specification 01."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The receiver is not\r\nrequired to complete delivery of the Application Message before sending the\r\nPUBREC or PUBCOMP. When its original sender receives the PUBREC packet, ownership\r\nof the Application Message is transferred to the receiver."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Figure 4.3"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "shows that there are two methods by which QoS 2 can be handled by the receiver.\r\nThey differ in the point within the flow at which the message is made available\r\nfor onward delivery. The choice of Method A or Method B is implementation\r\nspecific. As long as an implementation chooses exactly one of these approaches,\r\nthis does not affect the guarantees of a QoS 2 flow."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "4.4\r\nMessage delivery retry"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "When a Client reconnects\r\nwith CleanSession set to 0, both the Client and Server MUST re-send any\r\nunacknowledged PUBLISH Packets (where QoS > 0) and PUBREL Packets using\r\ntheir original Packet Identifiers"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.4.0-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "This is the only\r\ncircumstance where a Client or Server is REQUIRED to redeliver messages."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Non normative comment"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Historically retransmission of Control Packets was required to overcome data\r\nloss on some older TCP networks.\u00a0This might remain a concern where MQTT\r\n3.1.1 implementations are to be deployed in such environments."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "4.5 Message receipt"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/camp/camp-spec/v1.2/cs01/camp-spec-v1.2-cs01.html"}
