{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Voting History"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Cloud Application Management for Platforms Version 1.1"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Committee Specification 01"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "When a Server takes\r\nownership of an incoming Application Message it MUST add it to the Session\r\nstate of those clients that have matching Subscriptions. Matching rules are\r\ndefined in Section"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "4.7"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.5.0-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Under normal circumstances Clients receive messages in\r\nresponse to Subscriptions they have created. A Client could also receive\r\nmessages that do not match any of its explicit Subscriptions. This can happen\r\nif the Server automatically assigned a subscription to the Client. A Client\r\ncould also receive messages while an UNSUBSCRIBE operation is in progress."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Client MUST acknowledge any Publish Packet it\r\nreceives according to the applicable QoS rules regardless of whether it elects\r\nto process the Application Message that it contains"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.5.0-2]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "HTML"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "PDF"}
