{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Cloud Application Management for Platforms Version 1.1"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "4.6 Message ordering"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "A Client MUST follow these\r\nrules when implementing the protocol flows defined elsewhere in this chapter:"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "When it re-sends any\r\n     PUBLISH packets, it MUST re-send them in the order in which the original\r\n     PUBLISH packets were sent (this applies to QoS 1 and QoS 2 messages)"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.6.0-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "It MUST send PUBACK\r\n     packets in the order in which the corresponding PUBLISH packets were\r\n     received (QoS 1 messages)"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.6.0-2]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "It MUST send PUBREC\r\n     packets in the order in which the corresponding PUBLISH packets were\r\n     received (QoS 2 messages)"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.6.0-3]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "It MUST send PUBREL\r\n     packets in the order in which the corresponding PUBREC packets were\r\n     received (QoS 2 messages)"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.6.0-4]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "A Server MUST by default\r\ntreat each Topic as an \"Ordered Topic\". It MAY provide an\r\nadministrative or other mechanism to allow one or more Topics to be treated as\r\nan \"Unordered Topic\""}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": ". Edited by Jacques Durand, Adrian Otto, Gilbert Pilz, and Tom Rutt. 09 November 2014. OASIS Committee Specification 01."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/camp/camp-spec/v1.1/cs01/camp-spec-v1.1-cs01.html"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": ". Latest version:"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/camp/camp-spec/v1.1/camp-spec-v1.1.html"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "November 2014"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Voting History"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Cloud Application Management for Platforms (CAMP) Test Assertions Version 1.1"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Committee Specification 01"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "HTML"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.6.0-5]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "When a Server processes a\r\nmessage that has been published to an Ordered Topic, it MUST follow the rules\r\nlisted above when delivering messages to each of its subscribers. In addition\r\nit MUST send PUBLISH packets to consumers (for the same Topic and QoS) in the\r\norder that they were received from any given Client"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.6.0-6]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Non normative comment"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The rules listed above ensure that\r\nwhen a stream of messages is published and subscribed to with QoS 1, the final\r\ncopy of each message received by the subscribers will be in the order that they\r\nwere originally published in, but the possibility of message duplication could\r\nresult in a re-send of an earlier message being received after one of its\r\nsuccessor messages. For example a publisher might send messages in the order\r\n1,2,3,4 and the subscriber might receive them in the order 1,2,3,2,3,4."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If both Client and Server make sure\r\nthat no more than one message is \u201cin-flight\u201d at any one time (by not sending a\r\nmessage until its predecessor has been acknowledged), then no QoS 1 message\r\nwill be received after any later one - for example a subscriber might receive\r\nthem in the order 1,2,3,3,4 but not 1,2,3,2,3,4. Setting an in-flight window of\r\n1 also means that order will be preserved even if the publisher sends a\r\nsequence of messages with different QoS levels on the same topic."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "PDF"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "DOC"}
