{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "4.7\r\nTopic Names and Topic Filters"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "4.7.1 Topic wildcards"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The topic level separator is used to introduce structure\r\ninto the Topic Name. If present, it divides the Topic Name into multiple \u201ctopic\r\nlevels\u201d."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "A subscription\u2019s Topic Filter can contain special wildcard\r\ncharacters, which allow you to subscribe to multiple topics at once."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The wildcard characters can\r\nbe used in Topic Filters, but MUST NOT be used within a Topic Name"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.7.1-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "4.7.1.1 Topic level\r\nseparator"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The forward slash (\u2018/\u2019 U+002F) is used to separate each\r\nlevel within a topic tree and provide a hierarchical structure to the Topic Names.\r\nThe use of the topic level separator is significant when either of the two\r\nwildcard characters is encountered in Topic Filters specified by subscribing Clients.\r\nTopic level separators can appear anywhere in a Topic Filter or Topic Name.\r\nAdjacent Topic level separators indicate a zero length topic level."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "4.7.1.2 Multi-level\r\nwildcard"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/camp/camp-ta/v1.1/cs01/camp-ta-v1.1-cs01.html"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": ". Latest version:"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/camp/camp-ta/v1.1/camp-ta-v1.1.html"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "November 2014"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Voting History"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Code List Representation (Genericode) Version 1.0"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Committee Specification 01"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The number sign (\u2018#\u2019 U+0023) is a wildcard character that\r\nmatches any number of levels within a topic. The multi-level wildcard\r\nrepresents the parent and any number of child levels."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The multi-level wildcard character MUST be specified either on its own\r\nor following a topic level separator. In either case it MUST be the last\r\ncharacter specified in the Topic Filter"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.7.1-2]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Non normative comment"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "For example, if a Client subscribes\r\nto \u201csport/tennis/player1/#\u201d, it would receive messages published using these\r\ntopic names:"}
