{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": ". See Section 1.5.3"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "There is no limit to the number of levels in a Topic Name or\r\nTopic Filter, other than that imposed by the overall length of a UTF-8 encoded\r\nstring."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "When it performs\r\nsubscription matching the Server MUST NOT perform any normalization of Topic\r\nNames or Topic Filters, or any modification or substitution of unrecognized\r\ncharacters"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.7.3-4]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": ". Each\r\nnon-wildcarded level in the Topic Filter has to match the corresponding level\r\nin the Topic Name character for character for the match to succeed."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Non normative comment"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The UTF-8 encoding rules mean that\r\nthe comparison of Topic Filter and Topic Name could be performed either by\r\ncomparing the encoded UTF-8 bytes, or by comparing decoded Unicode\r\ncharacters"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Non normative comment"}
