{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": ". Edited by Ram Kumar. 11 November 2009. OASIS Committee Specification 01."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/ciq/v3.0/xPRL/cs01/specs/ciq-xprl-specs-cs01.html"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the Client or Server\r\nencounters a Transient Error while processing an inbound Control Packet it MUST\r\nclose the Network Connection on which it received that Control Packet"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.8.0-2]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": ". If a Server detects a Transient Error\r\nit SHOULD NOT disconnect or have any other effect on its interactions with any\r\nother Client."}
