{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[RFC5246]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "is used, SSL Certificates sent from the Server can be used by the Client to\r\nauthenticate the Server. Implementations providing MQTT service for multiple\r\nhostnames from a single IP address should be aware of the Server Name Indication\r\nextension to"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "TLS defined in section 3 of RFC 6066"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[RFC6066]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": ".This\r\nallows a Client to tell the Server the hostname of the Server it is trying to\r\nconnect to."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "An implementation might allow for authentication where the\r\ncredentials are sent in an Application Message from the Server to the Client."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "A VPN between Clients and Servers can provide confidence\r\nthat Clients are connecting to the intended Server."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "5.4.4 Integrity of Application\r\nMessages and Control Packets"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Applications can independently include hash values in their\r\nApplication Messages. This can provide integrity of the contents of Publish\r\nControl Packets across the network and at rest."}
