{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-1.5.3-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The character data in a UTF-8\r\n  encoded string MUST be well-formed UTF-8 as defined by the Unicode\r\n  specification [Unicode] and restated in RFC 3629 [RFC3629]. In particular\r\n  this data MUST NOT include encodings of code points between U+D800 and\r\n  U+DFFF. If a Server or Client receives a Control Packet containing ill-formed\r\n  UTF-8 it MUST close the Network Connection."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-1.5.3-2]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "A UTF-8 encoded string MUST NOT\r\n  include an encoding of the null character U+0000. If a receiver (Server or\r\n  Client) receives a Control Packet containing U+0000 it MUST close the Network\r\n  Connection."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-1.5.3-3]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "A UTF-8 encoded sequence 0xEF\r\n  0xBB 0xBF is always to be interpreted to mean U+FEFF (\"ZERO WIDTH\r\n  NO-BREAK SPACE\") wherever it appears in a string and MUST NOT be skipped\r\n  over or stripped off by a packet receiver."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-2.2.2-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Where a flag bit is marked as\r\n  \u201cReserved\u201d in Table 2.2 - Flag Bits, it is reserved for future use and MUST\r\n  be set to the value listed in that table."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-2.2.2-2]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If invalid flags are received,\r\n  the receiver MUST close the Network Connection."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Voting History"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Emergency Data Exchange Language (EDXL) Hospital AVailability Exchange (HAVE) Version 2.0"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Committee Specification 02"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "HL7 Informative Document"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "HTML"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "PDF"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "DOC"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "XML schemas"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Distribution ZIP file"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-2.3.1-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "SUBSCRIBE, UNSUBSCRIBE, and\r\n  PUBLISH (in cases where QoS > 0) Control Packets MUST contain a non-zero\r\n  16-bit Packet Identifier."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-2.3.1-2]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Each time a Client sends a new\r\n  packet of one of these types it MUST assign it a currently unused Packet\r\n  Identifier."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-2.3.1-3]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If a Client re-sends a\r\n  particular Control Packet, then it MUST use the same Packet Identifier in\r\n  subsequent re-sends of that packet. The Packet Identifier becomes available\r\n  for reuse after the Client has processed the corresponding acknowledgement\r\n  packet. In the case of a QoS 1 PUBLISH this is the corresponding PUBACK; in\r\n  the case of QO2 it is PUBCOMP. For SUBSCRIBE or UNSUBSCRIBE it is the\r\n  corresponding SUBACK or UNSUBACK."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-2.3.1-4]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The same conditions [MQTT-2.3.1-3]\r\n  apply to a Server when it sends a PUBLISH with QoS >0."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-2.3.1-5]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "A PUBLISH Packet MUST NOT\r\n  contain a Packet Identifier if its QoS value is set to 0."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "OASIS Emergency Management TC"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Cite as:"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "[EDXL-HAVE-v2.0]"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Emergency Data Exchange Language (EDXL) Hospital AVailability Exchange (HAVE) Version 2.0"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Edited by Darrell O\u2019Donnell, Brian Wilkins, Rex Brooks, and Scott M. Robertson. 18 March 2019."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "OASIS Committee Specification 02. HL7 Informative Document."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-2.3.1-6]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "A PUBACK, PUBREC or PUBREL\r\n  Packet MUST contain the same Packet Identifier as the PUBLISH Packet that was\r\n  originally sent."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-2.3.1-7]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Similarly to [MQTT-2.3.1-6],\r\n  SUBACK and UNSUBACK MUST contain the Packet Identifier that was used in the\r\n  corresponding SUBSCRIBE and UNSUBSCRIBE Packet respectively."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.0-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "After a Network Connection is\r\n  established by a Client to a Server, the first Packet sent from the Client to\r\n  the Server MUST be a CONNECT Packet."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.0-2]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Server MUST process a second\r\n  CONNECT Packet sent from a Client as a protocol violation and disconnect the\r\n  Client."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "https://docs.oasis-open.org/emergency/edxl-have/v2.0/cs02/edxl-have-v2.0-cs02.html"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Latest version:"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "https://docs.oasis-open.org/emergency/edxl-have/v2.0/edxl-have-v2.0.html"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "March 2019"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Voting History"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Emergency Data Exchange Language (EDXL) Hospital AVailability Exchange (HAVE) Version 2.0"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Committee Specification 01"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.2-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the protocol name is\r\n  incorrect the Server MAY disconnect the Client, or it MAY continue processing\r\n  the CONNECT packet in accordance with some other specification. In the latter\r\n  case, the Server MUST NOT continue to process the CONNECT packet in line with\r\n  this specification."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.2-2]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Server MUST respond to the\r\n  CONNECT Packet with a CONNACK return code 0x01 (unacceptable protocol level)\r\n  and then disconnect the Client if the Protocol Level is not supported by the\r\n  Server."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.2-3]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Server MUST validate that\r\n  the reserved flag in the CONNECT Control Packet is set to zero and disconnect\r\n  the Client if it is not zero."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.2-4]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If CleanSession is set to 0, the\r\n  Server MUST resume communications with the Client based on state from the\r\n  current Session (as identified by the Client identifier). If there is no\r\n  Session associated with the Client identifier the Server MUST create a new\r\n  Session. The Client and Server MUST store the Session after the Client and\r\n  Server are disconnected."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.2-5]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "After the disconnection of a\r\n  Session that had CleanSession set to 0, the Server MUST store further QoS 1\r\n  and QoS 2 messages that match any subscriptions that the client had at the\r\n  time of disconnection as part of the Session state."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.2-6]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If CleanSession is set to 1, the\r\n  Client and Server MUST discard any previous Session and start a new one. This\r\n  Session lasts as long as the Network Connection. State data associated with\r\n  this Session MUST NOT be reused in any subsequent Session."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "HL7 Informative Document"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "HTML"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "PDF"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "ODT"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "XML schemas"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Distribution ZIP file"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "OASIS Emergency Management TC"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Cite as:"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.2.7]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Retained messages do not form\r\n  part of the Session state in the Server, they MUST NOT be deleted when the\r\n  Session ends."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.2-8]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the Will Flag is set to 1 this indicates that, if the\r\n  Connect request is accepted, a Will Message MUST be stored on the Server and\r\n  associated with the Network Connection. The Will Message MUST be published\r\n  when the Network Connection is subsequently closed unless the Will Message\r\n  has been deleted by the Server on receipt of a DISCONNECT Packet."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.2-9]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the Will Flag is set to 1,\r\n  the Will QoS and Will Retain fields in the Connect Flags will be used by the\r\n  Server, and the Will Topic and Will Message fields MUST be present in the\r\n  payload."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.2-10]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Will Message MUST be removed\r\n  from the stored Session state in the Server once it has been published or the\r\n  Server has received a DISCONNECT packet from the Client."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "[EDXL-HAVE-v2.0]"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Emergency Data Exchange Language (EDXL) Hospital AVailability Exchange (HAVE) Version 2.0"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Edited by Darrell O\u2019Donnell, Brian Wilkins, Rex Brooks, and Scott M. Robertson. 13 December 2018."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "OASIS Committee Specification 01. HL7 Informative Document."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.2-11]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the Will Flag is set to 0 the\r\n  Will QoS and Will Retain fields in the Connect Flags MUST be set to zero and\r\n  the Will Topic and Will Message fields MUST NOT be present in the payload."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.2-12]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the Will Flag is set to 0, a\r\n  Will Message MUST NOT be published when this Network Connection ends."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.2-13]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the Will Flag is set to 0,\r\n  then the Will QoS MUST be set to 0 (0x00)."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.2-14]"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "https://docs.oasis-open.org/emergency/edxl-have/v2.0/cs01/edxl-have-v2.0-cs01.html"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Latest version:"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "https://docs.oasis-open.org/emergency/edxl-have/v2.0/edxl-have-v2.0.html"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "December 2018"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Voting History"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the Will Flag is set to 1,\r\n  the value of Will QoS can be 0 (0x00), 1 (0x01), or 2 (0x02). It MUST NOT be\r\n  3 (0x03)."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.2-15]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the Will Flag is set to 0,\r\n  then the Will Retain Flag MUST be set to 0."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.2-16]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the Will Flag is set to 1 and\r\n  If Will Retain is set to 0, the Server MUST publish the Will Message as a\r\n  non-retained message."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.2-17]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the Will Flag is set to 1 and\r\n  If Will Retain is set to 1, the Server MUST publish the Will Message as a\r\n  retained message."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.2-18]"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Emergency Data Exchange Language Situation Reporting (EDXL-SitRep) Version 1.0"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Committee Specification 02"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "HTML"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "PDF"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "ODT"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "XML schemas"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Example files"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Distribution ZIP file"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "OASIS Emergency Management TC"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Cite as:"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the User Name Flag is set to\r\n  0, a user name MUST NOT be present in the payload."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.2-19]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the User Name Flag is set to\r\n  1, a user name MUST be present in the payload."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.2-20]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the Password Flag is set to\r\n  0, a password MUST NOT be present in the payload."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.2-21]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the Password Flag is set to\r\n  1, a password MUST be present in the payload."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.2-22]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the User Name Flag is set to\r\n  0, the Password Flag MUST be set to 0."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.2-23]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "It is the responsibility of the\r\n  Client to ensure that the interval between Control Packets being sent does\r\n  not exceed the Keep Alive value. In the absence of sending any other Control\r\n  Packets, the Client MUST send a PINGREQ Packet."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.2-24]"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "[EDXL-SitRep]"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Emergency Data Exchange Language Situation Reporting (EDXL-SitRep) Version 1.0"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": ". Edited by Rex Brooks, Timothy Grapes, Werner Joerg, and Jeff Waters. 06 October 2016. OASIS Committee Specification 02."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/emergency/edxl-sitrep/v1.0/cs02/edxl-sitrep-v1.0-cs02.html"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": ". Latest version:"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/emergency/edxl-sitrep/v1.0/edxl-sitrep-v1.0.html"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the Keep Alive value is\r\n  non-zero and the Server does not receive a Control Packet from the Client\r\n  within one and a half times the Keep Alive time period, it MUST disconnect\r\n  the Network Connection to the Client as if the network had failed."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.3-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "These fields, if present, MUST\r\n  appear in the order Client Identifier, Will Topic, Will Message, User Name,\r\n  Password."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.3-2]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Each Client connecting to the\r\n  Server has a unique ClientId. The ClientId MUST be used by Clients and by\r\n  Servers to identify state that they hold relating to this MQTT Session\r\n  between the Client and the Server."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.3-3]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Client Identifier (ClientId)\r\n  MUST be present and MUST be the first field in the CONNECT packet payload."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.3-4]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The ClientId MUST be a UTF-8\r\n  encoded string as defined in Section"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "October 2016"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Voting History"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Encodings for OBIX: Common Encodings Version 1.0"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Committee Specification 01"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "HTML"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "PDF"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "DOC"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Distribution ZIP file"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "1.5.3"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.3-5]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The\r\n  Server MUST allow ClientIds which are between 1 and 23 UTF-8 encoded bytes in\r\n  length, and that contain only the characters"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "\"0123456789abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyzABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ\"."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.3-6]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "A Server MAY allow a Client to\r\n  supply a ClientId that has a length of zero bytes. However if it does so the\r\n  Server MUST treat this as a special case and assign a unique ClientId to that\r\n  Client. It MUST then process the CONNECT packet as if the Client had provided\r\n  that unique ClientId."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.3-7]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the Client supplies a\r\n  zero-byte ClientId, the Client MUST also set CleanSession to 1."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.3-8]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the Client supplies a zero-byte\r\n  ClientId with CleanSession set to 0, the Server MUST respond to the CONNECT\r\n  Packet with a CONNACK return code 0x02 (Identifier rejected) and then close\r\n  the Network Connection."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "OASIS Open Building Information Exchange (oBIX) TC"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Cite as:"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "[OBIX-Encodings]"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Encodings for OBIX: Common Encodings Version 1.0."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": ".  Edited by Markus Jung. 14 September 2015. OASIS Committee Specification 01."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/obix/obix-encodings/v1.0/cs01/obix-encodings-v1.0-cs01.html"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": ". Latest version:"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.3-9]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the Server rejects the\r\n  ClientId it MUST respond to the CONNECT Packet with a CONNACK return code\r\n  0x02 (Identifier rejected) and then close the Network Connection."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.3-10]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Will Topic MUST be a UTF-8\r\n  encoded string as defined in Section"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "\u200e"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "1.5.3."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.3-11]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The User Name MUST be a UTF-8\r\n  encoded string as defined in Section 1.5.3."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/obix/obix-encodings/v1.0/obix-encodings-v1.0.html"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "September 2015"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Voting History"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Emergency Data Exchange Language (EDXL) Tracking of Emergency Patients (TEP) Version 1.1"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Committee Specification 02"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "HTML"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "PDF"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "DOC"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "XML schemas"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Distribution ZIP file"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "OASIS Emergency Management TC"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.4-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Server MUST validate that\r\n  the CONNECT Packet conforms to section"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "3.1"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "and close the\r\n  Network Connection without sending a CONNACK if it does not conform."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.4-2]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the ClientId represents a\r\n  Client already connected to the Server then the Server MUST disconnect the\r\n  existing Client."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.4-3]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If CONNECT validation is successful the Server MUST\r\n  perform the processing of CleanSession that is described in section 3.1.2.4."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.4-4]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If CONNECT validation is\r\n  successful the Server MUST acknowledge the CONNECT Packet with a CONNACK\r\n  Packet containing a zero return code."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Cite as:"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "[EDXL-TEP-v1.1]"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Emergency Data Exchange Language (EDXL) Tracking of Emergency Patients (TEP) Version 1.1"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": ". Edited by Werner Joerg and Patti Iles Aymond. 21 September 2018. OASIS Committee Specification 02."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/emergency/edxl-tep/v1.1/cs02/edxl-tep-v1.1-cs02.html"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": ". Latest version:"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/emergency/edxl-tep/v1.1/edxl-tep-v1.1.html"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "September 2018"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.1.4-5]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the Server rejects the\r\n  CONNECT, it MUST NOT process any data sent by the Client after the CONNECT\r\n  Packet."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.2.0-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The first packet sent from the\r\n  Server to the Client MUST be a CONNACK Packet."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.2.2-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the Server accepts a\r\n  connection with CleanSession set to 1, the Server MUST set Session Present to\r\n  0 in the CONNACK packet in addition to setting a zero return code in the\r\n  CONNACK packet."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.2.2-2]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the Server accepts a\r\n  connection with CleanSession set to 0, the value set in Session Present\r\n  depends on whether the Server already has stored Session state for the\r\n  supplied client ID. If the Server has stored Session state, it MUST set\r\n  Session\u00a0Present to 1 in the CONNACK packet."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.2.2-3]"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Voting History"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Emergency Data Exchange Language (EDXL) Tracking of Emergency Patients (TEP) Version 1.1"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Committee Specification 01"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "HTML"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "PDF"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "ODT"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "XML schemas"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Distribution ZIP file"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "OASIS Emergency Management TC"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Cite as:"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the Server does not have\r\n  stored Session state, it MUST set Session Present to 0 in the CONNACK packet.\r\n  This is in addition to setting a zero return code in the CONNACK packet."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.2.2-4]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If a server sends a CONNACK\r\n  packet containing a non-zero return code it MUST set Session Present to 0."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.2.2-5]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If a server sends a CONNACK\r\n  packet containing a non-zero return code it MUST then close the Network\r\n  Connection."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.2.2-6]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If none of the return codes listed\r\n  in"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Table 3.1"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "\u2013 Connect Return code\r\n  values"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "are deemed applicable, then the Server MUST\r\n  close the Network Connection without sending a CONNACK."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.3.1-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The DUP flag MUST be set to 1 by\r\n  the Client or Server when it attempts to re-deliver a PUBLISH Packet."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.3.1-2]"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "[EDXL-TEP-v1.1]"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Emergency Data Exchange Language (EDXL) Tracking of Emergency Patients (TEP) Version 1.1"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": ". Edited by Werner Joerg and Patti Lles Aymond. 20 January 2016. OASIS Committee Specification 01."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/emergency/edxl-tep/v1.1/cs01/edxl-tep-v1.1-cs01.html"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": ". Latest version:"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/emergency/edxl-tep/v1.1/edxl-tep-v1.1.html"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The DUP flag MUST be set to 0\r\n  for all QoS 0 messages."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.3.1-3]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The value of the DUP flag from\r\n  an incoming PUBLISH packet is not propagated when the PUBLISH Packet is sent\r\n  to subscribers by the Server. The DUP flag in the outgoing PUBLISH packet is\r\n  set independently to the incoming PUBLISH packet,"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "its value MUST be\r\n  determined solely by whether the outgoing PUBLISH packet is a retransmission"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "January 2016"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Voting History"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Encodings for OBIX: Common Encodings Version 1.0"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Committee Specification 01"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "HTML"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "PDF"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "DOC"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Distribution ZIP file"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "OASIS Open Building Information Exchange (oBIX) TC"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Cite as:"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.3.1-4]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "A PUBLISH Packet MUST NOT have\r\n  both QoS bits set to 1. If a Server or Client receives a PUBLISH Packet which\r\n  has both QoS bits set to 1 it MUST close the Network Connection."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.3.1-5]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the RETAIN flag is set to 1,\r\n  in a PUBLISH Packet sent by a Client to a Server, the Server MUST store the Application\r\n  Message and its QoS, so that it can be delivered to future subscribers whose\r\n  subscriptions match its topic name."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.3.1-6]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "When a new subscription is\r\n  established, the last retained message, if any, on each matching topic name\r\n  MUST be sent to the subscriber."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.3.1-7]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the Server receives a QoS 0 message with the RETAIN flag set\r\n  to 1 it MUST discard any message previously retained for that topic. It\r\n  SHOULD store the new QoS 0 message as the new retained message for that\r\n  topic, but MAY choose to discard it at any time - if this happens there will\r\n  be no retained message for that topic."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.3.1-8]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "When sending a PUBLISH Packet to\r\n  a Client the Server MUST set the RETAIN flag to 1 if a message is sent as a\r\n  result of a new subscription being made by a Client."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "[OBIX-Encodings]"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Encodings for OBIX: Common Encodings Version 1.0."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": ".  Edited by Markus Jung. 14 September 2015. OASIS Committee Specification 01."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/obix/obix-encodings/v1.0/cs01/obix-encodings-v1.0-cs01.html"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": ". Latest version:"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/obix/obix-encodings/v1.0/obix-encodings-v1.0.html"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.3.1-9]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "It MUST set the RETAIN flag to 0\r\n  when a PUBLISH Packet is sent to a Client because it matches an established\r\n  subscription regardless of how the flag was set in the message it received."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.3.1-10]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "A PUBLISH Packet with a RETAIN\r\n  flag set to 1 and a payload containing zero bytes will be processed as normal\r\n  by the Server and sent to Clients with a subscription matching the topic\r\n  name. Additionally any existing retained message with the same topic name\r\n  MUST be removed and any future subscribers for the topic will not receive a\r\n  retained message."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.3.1-11]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "A zero byte retained message\r\n  MUST NOT be stored as a retained message on the Server."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.3.1-12]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the RETAIN flag is 0, in a\r\n  PUBLISH Packet sent by a Client to a Server, the Server MUST NOT store the\r\n  message and MUST NOT remove or replace any existing retained message."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.3.2-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Topic Name MUST be present\r\n  as the first field in the PUBLISH Packet Variable header. It MUST be a UTF-8\r\n  encoded string."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "September 2015"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Voting History"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Energy Market Information Exchange (EMIX) Version 1.0"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Committee Specification 02"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "HTML"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "PDF"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "DOC"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "XML schemas"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Distribution ZIP file"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "OASIS Energy Market Information Exchange (eMIX) TC"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.3.2-2]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Topic Name in the PUBLISH\r\n  Packet MUST NOT contain wildcard characters."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.3.2-3]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Topic Name in a PUBLISH\r\n  Packet sent by a Server to a subscribing Client MUST match the Subscription\u2019s\r\n  Topic Filter according to the matching process defined in Section 4.7."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.3.4-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The receiver of a PUBLISH Packet\r\n  MUST respond according to Table 3.4 - Expected Publish Packet response as\r\n  determined by the QoS in the PUBLISH Packet."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.3.5-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Server MUST deliver the\r\n  message to the Client respecting the maximum QoS of all the matching subscriptions."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.3.5-2]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If a Server implementation does\r\n  not authorize a PUBLISH to be performed by a Client; it has no way of\r\n  informing that Client. It MUST either make a positive acknowledgement,\r\n  according to the normal QoS rules, or close the Network Connection."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.6.1-1]"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Cite as:"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "[EMIX-v1.0]"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Energy Market Information Exchange (EMIX) Version 1.0"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": ". Edited by Toby Considine. 11 January 2012. OASIS Committee Specification 02."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/emix/emix/v1.0/cs02/emix-v1.0-cs02.html"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": ". Latest version:"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Bits 3,2,1 and 0 of the fixed\r\n  header in the PUBREL Control Packet are reserved and MUST be set to 0,0,1 and\r\n  0 respectively. The Server MUST treat any other value as malformed and close\r\n  the Network Connection."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.8.1-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Bits 3,2,1 and 0 of the fixed\r\n  header of the SUBSCRIBE Control Packet are reserved and MUST be set to 0,0,1\r\n  and 0 respectively. The Server MUST treat any other value as malformed and\r\n  close the Network Connection."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.8.3-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Topic Filters in a SUBSCRIBE\r\n  packet payload MUST be UTF-8 encoded strings as defined in Section 1.5.3."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.8.3-2]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the Server chooses not to\r\n  support topic filters that contain wildcard characters it MUST reject any\r\n  Subscription request whose filter contains them."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.8.3-3]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The payload of a SUBSCRIBE\r\n  packet MUST contain at least one Topic Filter / QoS pair. A SUBSCRIBE packet\r\n  with no payload is a protocol violation."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/emix/emix/v1.0/emix-v1.0.html"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "January 2012"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Voting History"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Exchange Header Envelope (XHE) Version 1.0"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Committee Specification 01"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3-8.3-4]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Server MUST treat a\r\n  SUBSCRIBE packet as malformed and close the Network Connection if any of\r\n  Reserved bits in the payload are non-zero, or QoS is not 0,1 or 2."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.8.4-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "When the Server receives a\r\n  SUBSCRIBE Packet from a Client, the Server MUST respond with a SUBACK Packet."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.8.4-2]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The SUBACK Packet MUST have the\r\n  same Packet Identifier as the SUBSCRIBE Packet that it is acknowledging."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.8.4-3]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If a Server receives a SUBSCRIBE\r\n  Packet containing a Topic Filter that is identical to an existing\r\n  Subscription\u2019s Topic Filter then it MUST completely replace that existing\r\n  Subscription with a new Subscription. The Topic Filter in the new\r\n  Subscription will be identical to that in the previous Subscription, although\r\n  its maximum QoS value could be different. Any existing retained messages\r\n  matching the Topic Filter MUST be re-sent, but the flow of publications MUST\r\n  NOT be interrupted."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.8.4-4]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If a Server receives a SUBSCRIBE\r\n  packet that contains multiple Topic Filters it MUST handle that packet as if\r\n  it had received a sequence of multiple SUBSCRIBE packets, except that it\r\n  combines their responses into a single SUBACK response."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.8.4-5]"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "HTML"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "PDF"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "XML"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Distribution ZIP file"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "OASIS Business Document Exchange (BDXR) TC"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The SUBACK Packet\r\n  sent by the Server to the Client MUST contain a return code for each Topic\r\n  Filter/QoS pair. This return code MUST either show the maximum QoS that was\r\n  granted for that Subscription or indicate that the subscription failed."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.8.4-6]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Server might grant a lower\r\n  maximum QoS than the subscriber requested. The QoS of Payload Messages sent\r\n  in response to a Subscription MUST be the minimum of the QoS of the\r\n  originally published message and the maximum QoS granted by the Server. The\r\n  server is permitted to send duplicate copies of a message to a subscriber in\r\n  the case where the original message was published with QoS 1 and the maximum\r\n  QoS granted was QoS 0."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.9.3-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The order of return codes in the\r\n  SUBACK Packet MUST match the order of Topic Filters in the SUBSCRIBE Packet."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.9.3-2]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "SUBACK return codes other than\r\n  0x00, 0x01, 0x02 and 0x80 are reserved and MUST NOT be used."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Cite as:"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "[XHE-V1.0]"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Exchange Header Envelope (XHE) Version 1.0"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": ". Edited by G. Ken Holman. 21 March 2019. OASIS Committee Specification 01."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "https://docs.oasis-open.org/bdxr/xhe/v1.0/cs01/xhe-v1.0-cs01-oasis.html"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": ". Latest version:"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.10.1-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Bits 3,2,1 and 0 of the fixed\r\n  header of the UNSUBSCRIBE Control Packet are reserved and MUST be set to\r\n  0,0,1 and 0 respectively. The Server MUST treat any other value as malformed\r\n  and close the Network Connection."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.10.3-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Topic Filters in an UNSUBSCRIBE packet MUST be UTF-8 encoded\r\n  strings as defined in Section 1.5.3, packed contiguously."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.10.3-2]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Payload of an UNSUBSCRIBE\r\n  packet MUST contain at least one Topic Filter. An UNSUBSCRIBE packet with no\r\n  payload is a protocol violation."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.10.4-1]"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "https://docs.oasis-open.org/bdxr/xhe/v1.0/xhe-v1.0-oasis.html"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "March 2019"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Voting History"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Field Force Management Integration Interface Specification Version 1.0"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Committee Specification 01"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "HTML"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "PDF"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "DOC"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Topic Filters (whether they\r\n  contain wildcards or not) supplied in an UNSUBSCRIBE packet MUST be compared\r\n  character-by-character with the current set of Topic Filters held by the\r\n  Server for the Client. If any filter matches exactly then its owning\r\n  Subscription is deleted, otherwise no additional processing occurs."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.10.4-2]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If a Server deletes a\r\n  Subscription It MUST stop adding any new messages for delivery to the Client."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.10.4-3]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If a Server deletes a\r\n  Subscription It MUST complete the delivery of any QoS 1 or QoS 2 messages\r\n  which it has started to send to the Client."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.10.4-4]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Server MUST respond to an\r\n  UNSUBSUBCRIBE request by sending an UNSUBACK packet. The UNSUBACK Packet MUST\r\n  have the same Packet Identifier as the UNSUBSCRIBE Packet."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.10.4-5]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Even where no Topic\r\n  Subscriptions are deleted, the Server MUST respond with an UNSUBACK."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.10.4-6]"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "XML schemas"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "WSLD files"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Distribution ZIP file"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Field Force Management Integration Interface Specification Version 1.0"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Cite as:"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "[FFMII-SPEC-v1.0]"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Field Force Management Integration Interface Specification Version 1.0"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": ". Edited by Thinh Nguyenphu. 05 October 2012. OASIS Committee Specification 01."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If a Server receives an\r\n  UNSUBSCRIBE packet that contains multiple Topic Filters it MUST handle that\r\n  packet as if it had received a sequence of multiple UNSUBSCRIBE packets,\r\n  except that it sends just one UNSUBACK response."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.12.4-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Server MUST send a PINGRESP\r\n  Packet in response to a PINGREQ packet."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.14.1-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Server MUST validate that\r\n  reserved bits are set to zero and disconnect the Client if they are not zero."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.14.4-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "After sending a DISCONNECT\r\n  Packet the Client MUST close the Network Connection."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.14.4-2]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "After sending a DISCONNECT\r\n  Packet the Client MUST NOT send any more Control Packets on that Network\r\n  Connection."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/ffm/FFMII-SPEC/v1.0/cs01/FFMII-SPEC-v1.0-cs01.html"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": ". Latest version:"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/ffm/FFMII-SPEC/v1.0/FFMII-SPEC-v1.0.html"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "October 2012"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Voting History"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-3.14.4-3]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "On receipt of DISCONNECT the\r\n  Server MUST discard any Will Message associated with the current connection\r\n  without publishing it, as described in Section"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "3.1.2.5"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.1.0-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Client and Server MUST store\r\n  Session state for the entire duration of the Session."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.1.0-2]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "A Session MUST last at least as\r\n  long it has an active Network Connection."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.3.1-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "In the QoS 0 delivery protocol, the\r\n  Sender"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "\u00b7"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Identity Provider Discovery Service Protocol and Profile"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Committee Specification 01"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "HTML"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "PDF"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "ODT"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "OASIS Security Services TC"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Cite as:"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "[SAML-idp-discovery]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "MUST send a PUBLISH packet with\r\n  QoS=0, DUP=0."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.3.2-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "In the QoS 1 delivery protocol,\r\n  the Sender"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "\u00b7"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "MUST assign an unused Packet\r\n  Identifier each time it has a new Application Message to publish."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "\u00b7"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "MUST send a PUBLISH Packet containing\r\n  this Packet Identifier with QoS=1, DUP=0."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "\u00b7"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "MUST treat the PUBLISH Packet as\r\n  \"unacknowledged\" until it has received the corresponding PUBACK\r\n  packet from the receiver. See Section"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "4.4"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "for a discussion of\r\n  unacknowledged messages."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.3.2-2]"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Identity Provider Discovery Service Protocol and Profile"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": ". Edited by Rod Widdowson and Scott Cantor. 27 March 2008. OASIS Committee Specification 01."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/security/saml/Post2.0/sstc-saml-idp-discovery-cs-01.html"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": ". Latest version:"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/security/saml/Post2.0/sstc-saml-idp-discovery.html"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "In the QoS 1 delivery protocol,\r\n  the Receiver"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "MUST respond with a PUBACK Packet\r\n       containing the Packet Identifier from the incoming PUBLISH Packet,\r\n       having accepted ownership of the Application Message."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "After it has sent a PUBACK Packet\r\n       the Receiver MUST treat any incoming PUBLISH packet that contains the\r\n       same Packet Identifier as being a new publication, irrespective of the\r\n       setting of its DUP flag."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.3.3-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "In the QoS 2 delivery protocol,\r\n  the Sender"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "MUST assign an unused Packet\r\n       Identifier when it has a new Application Message to publish."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "MUST send a PUBLISH packet\r\n       containing this Packet Identifier with QoS=2, DUP=0."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "MUST treat the PUBLISH packet as\r\n       \"unacknowledged\" until it has received the corresponding\r\n       PUBREC packet from the receiver. See Section 4.4 for a discussion of unacknowledged messages."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "MUST send a PUBREL packet when it\r\n       receives a PUBREC packet from the receiver. This PUBREL packet MUST\r\n       contain the same Packet Identifier as the original PUBLISH packet."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "March 2008"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Voting History"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "JSON Profile of XACML 3.0 Version 1.1"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Committee Specification 01"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "HTML"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "MUST treat the PUBREL packet as\r\n       \"unacknowledged\" until it has received the corresponding\r\n       PUBCOMP packet from the receiver."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "MUST NOT re-send the PUBLISH once it\r\n       has sent the corresponding PUBREL packet."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.3.3-2]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "In the QoS 2\r\n  delivery protocol, the Receiver"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "MUST respond with a PUBREC\r\n       containing the Packet Identifier from the incoming PUBLISH Packet,\r\n       having accepted ownership of the Application Message."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Until it has received the\r\n       corresponding PUBREL packet, the Receiver MUST acknowledge any\r\n       subsequent PUBLISH packet with the same Packet Identifier by sending a\r\n       PUBREC. It MUST NOT cause duplicate messages to be delivered to any\r\n       onward recipients in this case."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "MUST respond to a PUBREL packet by\r\n       sending a PUBCOMP packet containing the same Packet Identifier as the\r\n       PUBREL."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "After it has sent a PUBCOMP, the\r\n       receiver MUST treat any subsequent PUBLISH packet that contains that\r\n       Packet Identifier as being a new publication."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "PDF"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "DOC"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Distribution ZIP file"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "OASIS eXtensible Access Control Markup Language (XACML) TC"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Cite as:"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "[xacml-json-v1.1]"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "JSON Profile of XACML 3.0 Version 1.1"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": ". Edited by David Brossard and Steven Legg. 05 December 2018. OASIS Committee Specification 01."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "https://docs.oasis-open.org/xacml/xacml-json-http/v1.1/cs01/xacml-json-http-v1.1-cs01.html"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.4.0-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "When a Client reconnects with\r\n  CleanSession set to 0, both the Client and Server MUST re-send any\r\n  unacknowledged PUBLISH Packets (where QoS > 0) and PUBREL Packets using\r\n  their original Packet Identifiers"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.5.0-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "When a Server takes ownership of\r\n  an incoming Application Message it MUST add it to the Session state of those\r\n  clients that have matching Subscriptions. Matching rules are defined in\r\n  Section 4.7."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.5.0-2]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Client MUST acknowledge any\r\n  Publish Packet it receives according to the applicable QoS rules regardless\r\n  of whether it elects to process the Application Message that it contains."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.6.0-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "When it re-sends any PUBLISH\r\n  packets, it MUST re-send them in the order in which the original PUBLISH\r\n  packets were sent (this applies to QoS 1 and QoS 2 messages)."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.6.0-2]"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Latest version:"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "https://docs.oasis-open.org/xacml/xacml-json-http/v1.1/xacml-json-http-v1.1.html"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "December 2018"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Voting History"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "JSON Profile of XACML 3.0 Version 1.0"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Committee Specification 01"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "HTML"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Client MUST send PUBACK packets\r\n  in the order in which the corresponding PUBLISH packets were received (QoS 1\r\n  messages)."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.6.0-3]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Client MUST send PUBREC packets\r\n  in the order in which the corresponding PUBLISH packets were received (QoS 2\r\n  messages)."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.6.0-4]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Client MUST send PUBREL packets\r\n  in the order in which the corresponding PUBREC packets were received (QoS 2\r\n  messages)."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.6.0-5]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "A Server MUST by default treat\r\n  each Topic as an \"Ordered Topic\". It MAY provide an administrative\r\n  or other mechanism to allow one or more Topics to be treated as an\r\n  \"Unordered Topic\"."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.6.0-6]"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "PDF"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "DOC"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Distribution ZIP file"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "OASIS eXtensible Access Control Markup Language (XACML) TC"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Cite as:"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "[xacml-json-v1.0]"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "JSON Profile of XACML 3.0 Version 1.0"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": ". Edited by David Brossard. 11 December 2014. OASIS Committee Specification 01."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/xacml/xacml-json-http/v1.0/cs01/xacml-json-http-v1.0-cs01.html"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "When a Server processes a\r\n  message that has been published to an Ordered Topic, it MUST follow the rules\r\n  listed above when delivering messages to each of its subscribers. In addition\r\n  it MUST send PUBLISH packets to consumers (for the same Topic and QoS) in the\r\n  order that they were received from any given Client."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.7.1-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The wildcard characters can be\r\n  used in Topic Filters, but MUST NOT be used within a Topic Name."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.7.1-2]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The multi-level wildcard\r\n  character MUST be specified either on its own or following a topic level\r\n  separator. In either case it MUST be the last character specified in the\r\n  Topic Filter."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.7.1-3]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The single-level wildcard can be\r\n  used at any level in the Topic Filter, including first and last levels. Where\r\n  it is used it MUST occupy an entire level of the filter."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.7.2-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The Server MUST NOT match Topic\r\n  Filters starting with a wildcard character (# or +) with Topic Names\r\n  beginning with a $ character."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.7.3-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "All Topic Names and Topic\r\n  Filters MUST be at least one character long."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.7.3-2]"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": ". Latest version:"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/xacml/xacml-json-http/v1.0/xacml-json-http-v1.0.html"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "December 2014"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Voting History"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Key Management Interoperability Protocol Profiles Version 2.0"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Committee Specification 01"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "HTML"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "PDF"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "DOCX"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Topic Names and Topic Filters\r\n  MUST NOT include the null character (Unicode U+0000)."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.7.3-3]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Topic Names and Topic Filters\r\n  are UTF-8 encoded strings, they MUST NOT encode to more than 65535 bytes."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.7.3-4]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "When it performs subscription matching the Server MUST NOT\r\n  perform any normalization of Topic Names or Topic Filters, or any\r\n  modification or substitution of unrecognized characters."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.8.0-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Unless stated otherwise, if\r\n  either the Server or Client encounters a protocol violation, it MUST close\r\n  the Network Connection on which it received that Control Packet which caused\r\n  the protocol violation."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-4.8.0-2]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "If the Client or Server\r\n  encounters a Transient Error while processing an inbound Control Packet it\r\n  MUST close the Network Connection on which it received that Control Packet."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-6.0.0-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "MQTT Control Packets MUST be\r\n  sent in WebSocket binary data frames. If any other type of data frame is\r\n  received the recipient MUST close the Network Connection."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Test cases"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Distribution ZIP file"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "OASIS Key Management Interoperability Protocol (KMIP) TC"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Cite as:"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "[kmip-profiles-v2.0]"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "Key Management Interoperability Protocol Profiles Version 2.0"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": ". Edited by Tim Hudson and Robert Lockhart. 12 June 2019. OASIS Committee Specification 01."}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": "https://docs.oasis-open.org/kmip/kmip-profiles/v2.0/cs01/kmip-profiles-v2.0-cs01.html"}
{"link": "https://www.oasis-open.org/standards", "text": ". Latest version:"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-6.0.0-2]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "A single WebSocket data frame\r\n  can contain multiple or partial MQTT Control Packets. The receiver MUST NOT\r\n  assume that MQTT Control Packets are aligned on WebSocket frame boundaries."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-6.0.0-3]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The client MUST include \u201cmqtt\u201d\r\n  in the list of WebSocket Sub Protocols it offers."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-6.0.0-4]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "The WebSocket Sub Protocol name\r\n  selected and returned by the server MUST be \u201cmqtt\u201d."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-7.0.0-1]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "A Server that both accepts\r\n  inbound connections and establishes outbound connections to other Servers\r\n  MUST conform as both an MQTT Client and MQTT Server."}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "[MQTT-7.0.0-2]"}
{"link": "http://docs.oasis-open.org/mqtt/mqtt/v3.1.1/os/mqtt-v3.1.1-os.html", "text": "Conformant implementations MUST\r\n  NOT require the use of any extensions defined outside of this specification\r\n  in order to interoperate with any other conformant implementation."}
